tent":{"case_id":"arb-ex08a-20260630060031","member_id":"C1","ok":true,"result":{"evidence":[{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T06:12:37Z","evidence_id":"ev_07b7be066555_submitted-evidence-03-defendant-07b7be066555","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-03-defendant-07b7be066555.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Adverse-authenticity source for defense merits argument. It reports a close family member disputing authorship and explains why; it also includes facts relevant to source-chain weight and counterweight to the forgery theory.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T06:15:30Z","sha256":"07b7be066555a0766c37ccbbcf15609c676a715461493dbe8752b25128e635c9","size_bytes":3705,"source_description":"Relevant text extracted from Business Insider article by Jacob Shamsian, published 2026-05-08T20:44:17.764Z, retrieved during defendant investigation on 2026-06-30 UTC. Extract preserves Mark Epstein's forgery challenge, note provenance as reported, and caveats that cut both ways including prior sealing and absence from DOJ/IG materials.","source_url":"https://www.businessinsider.com/jeffrey-epstein-brother-says-suicide-note-forgery-little-rascals-2026-5","storage_name":"07/07b7be066555a0766c37ccbbcf15609c676a715461493dbe8752b25128e635c9","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"Business Insider report on Mark Epstein forgery challenge and note provenance - relevant extract"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T06:09:23Z","evidence_id":"ev_87eda7a5f14d_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-87eda7a5f14d","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-87eda7a5f14d.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Official court order is the primary source showing a U.S. District Judge granted unsealing of the note before the May 8 deadline and describes the note's claimed provenance while using caveating language relevant to weight.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T06:08:00Z","sha256":"87eda7a5f14da6f6492443d9e3e63d5a5cbb1e7d75ae0a49c7f6d7f1cb254511","size_bytes":3043,"source_description":"Relevant text extracted from official Southern District of New York PDF order dated May 6, 2026, retrieved during plaintiff investigation on 2026-06-30 UTC. Local downloaded PDF sha256 observed: 7225441cb802084e2b9485ebc2c6d246fbfa08e109fe650cb14f445dc4745ca0; size 128,992 bytes. Extract preserves the parts material to unsealing, provenance, and caveats.","source_url":"https://www.nysd.uscourts.gov/sites/default/files/2026-05/16cr832%20-%20Tartaglione%20Order%20-%2026.5.6.pdf","storage_name":"87/87eda7a5f14da6f6492443d9e3e63d5a5cbb1e7d75ae0a49c7f6d7f1cb254511","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"SDNY unsealing order in United States v. Tartaglione, No. 16-CR-832 (KMK) - relevant extract"},{"admissibility_status":"case_packet","created_at":"2026-06-30T06:00:50Z","evidence_id":"ev_90fa205907f7_market-page","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"market-page.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","sha256":"90fa205907f7af6483463b7dcda6e06a38a2e22fbe19312319fdf46a78f14646","size_bytes":4641,"source_description":"Initial case packet file","storage_name":"90/90fa205907f7af6483463b7dcda6e06a38a2e22fbe19312319fdf46a78f14646","submitted_by_role":"system","submitted_phase":"case_packet","text_readable":true,"title":"market-page.txt"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T06:09:47Z","evidence_id":"ev_a2ccbb719d1f_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-a2ccbb719d1f","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-a2ccbb719d1f.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Credible reporting source showing the note was made public on May 6, 2026, describing it as purportedly written by Epstein, giving reported note text and circumstances, and preserving adverse caveats about authorship and official records.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T06:08:30Z","sha256":"a2ccbb719d1fab06be2d4b91c78b80fbaeef2c1c58aa8920fb6856caaa98bf13","size_bytes":2579,"source_description":"Relevant text extracted from PBS NewsHour article carrying Associated Press reporting by Michael R. Sisak and Larry Neumeister. Retrieved as HTML on 2026-06-30 UTC; local downloaded HTML sha256 observed: 7bc6354f83080c555ecb4ab0c17eb26bde83c6a1830ad012aed37e0122008e3b; size 246,650 bytes. Extract omits navigation, donation prompts, and unrelated page chrome.","source_url":"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/judge-releases-note-that-cellmate-says-he-found-after-epsteins-suspected-suicide-attempt","storage_name":"a2/a2ccbb719d1fab06be2d4b91c78b80fbaeef2c1c58aa8920fb6856caaa98bf13","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"PBS NewsHour / Associated Press report on Epstein note release - relevant extract"}]},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T06:34:17.146437908Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C1","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C1","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":879029,"role_id":"council","turn_number":9}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"list_evidence"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782800378118},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that I have reviewed the case details and evidence, I'll analyze the key points to make my decision.\n\nBased on my review of the arbitration record:\n\n1. The proposition is: \"By May 8, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent communication had been made publicly available.\"\n\n2. Key admitted evidence includes:\n   - PX-1 (case packet): Defines the market rule requiring \"a message or note written by Jeffrey Epstein, intended as a suicide note, [to] be made publicly available by the listed date\"\n   - PX-2 (SDNY order): Shows a May 6, 2026 court order granting unsealing of \"an alleged suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\" \n   - PX-3 (AP/PBS report): Reports the note was made public on May 6, 2026, describing it as \"a note purported to be written by Jeffrey Epstein\"\n   - D-1 (Business Insider): Reports Mark Epstein claiming the note is a forgery, but also contains counterweights\n\n3. All sides acknowledge that public availability occurred before the May 8 deadline: the SDNY court order dates to May 6, 2026, and the AP/PBS report was published May 6, 2026 (updated May 7).\n\n4. The core dispute concerns the \"credible reporting\" requirement for authorship. While PX-2 and PX-3 both use caveat language (\"alleged,\" \"purported,\" \"claimed\"), the plaintiff argues this satisfies the \"credibly reported\" standard under a preponderance standard, since it comes from official court sources and major news outlets.\n\n5. Both sides agree that the note contains content consistent with a suicide/final message (\"choosing the time to say goodbye,\" \"NO FUN,\" \"NOT WORTH IT\").\n\nDespite the caveats in the reporting, the evidence shows that:\n- The SDNY court specifically referenced an \"allegued suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\"\n- The AP/PBS report described it as a note \"purported to be written by Jeffrey Epstein\" \n- This constitutes \"credible reporting\" as defined in the market terms, even though it carries caveats\n\nOn balance, given the preponderance of evidence standard and the specific language of the market rule which accounts for \"credibly reported\" rather than definitively proven authorship, the evidence supports that the note was credibly reported to have been written by Epstein and intended as a suicide/communication note made publicly available before the deadline.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7f1cd56a73b649369de7bda9","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows by a preponderance of evidence that a note was officially unsealed by a federal court and credibly reported by AP/PBS as purportedly written by Epstein and intended as a suicide/final message, made publicly available before May 8, 2026 deadline. Though caveats exist, the market rule explicitly accounts for 'credibly reported' authorship rather than definitive proof.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":2143,"output":682,"cacheRead":31552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34377,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782800378119,"responseId":"gen-1782800378-CMkkEgAuydOGaNUMlkjp"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7f1cd56a73b649369de7bda9","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex08a-20260630060031\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C1\nremaining_ms: 865845\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex08a-20260630060031\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T06:34:17.146437908Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":865845,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":9}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex08a-20260630060031\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C1\nremaining_ms: 865845\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex08a-20260630060031\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T06:34:17.146437908Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":865845,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":9}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex08a-20260630060031","member_id":"C1","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-30T06:34:17.146437908Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C1","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C1","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":865845,"role_id":"council","turn_number":9}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782800391302},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote has been accepted. As council member C1, I voted that the proposition was \"demonstrated\" based on the admitted record evidence. The rationale was that the record shows by a preponderance of evidence that a note was officially unsealed by a federal court and credibly reported by AP/PBS as purportedly written by Epstein and intended as a suicide/final message, made publicly available before May 8, 2026 deadline. Though caveats exist, the market rule explicitly accounts for 'credibly reported' authorship rather than definitive proof."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":944,"output":117,"cacheRead":33664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782800391303,"responseId":"gen-1782800391-3BOFZSY2R3n6IsyTFMMf"}],"willRetry":false}
